      <odd id="aspace_8aa664eb1ff757ea78d008ad5ef5c909">
         <head>General note</head>
         <p>Forms part of Yale Record Group 37 (YRG 37), Records of associations, institutes, centers, and organizations affiliated with Yale University.</p>  
      </odd>
      <altformavail id="aspace_ce163c4485b4596cd12d1374520795ec">
         <head>Existence and Location of Copies</head>
         <p>The records are available on microfilm (504 frames on 1 reel, 35mm.) from Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library, at cost. Order no. HM171.</p>  
      </altformavail>
      <accessrestrict id="aspace_3ffd3e6eda04c16fbf41b0995bd54452">
         <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
         <p>The materials are open for research. Patrons must use HM 171 instead of the originals.</p>  
      </accessrestrict>
      <prefercite id="aspace_5ec12338cf6b296760b608f17dd8675d">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>General Hospital Society of Connecticut Records (RU 473). Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.</p>  
      </prefercite>
      <processinfo id="aspace_f7f64912dae2d7b3ccaea68eb066273a">
         <head>Processing Information</head>
         <p>Yale University records are arranged and described at the accession level by the creating office. The University Archives creates collection level descriptive records, but typically does no further arrangement and description at the accession level.</p>  
      </processinfo>
      <bioghist id="aspace_788f16fdab2efeb47eb24071c9ea81dc">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>The General Hospital Society of Connecticut was founded in 1826. Its name was changed to New Haven Hospital in 1884; Grace-New Haven Hospital in 1945; and Yale-New Haven Hospital in 1965. It served as the primary teaching hospital for the Yale medical school.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_6e9df1531b27854c14b64570a6008697">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The records consist of minutes, chapter records, and account books documenting the operations of the General Hospital Society of Connecticut (later known as New Haven Hospital).</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement id="aspace_769d628232484ecb75640ad511ca6793">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>The records are arranged by record type.</p>  
      </arrangement>
